sentences: John Paul White (born August 4, 1972) is an American singer-songwriter, and was a member of the Grammy Award-winning duo The Civil Wars.
He restarted his solo career with his 2016 release, Beulah.
White released the album The Long Goodbye in 2008.
The following year, White joined Joy Williams to form The Civil Wars.
The duo won the 2012 Grammy Awards for best Folk Album, and Country Performance by a Duo or Group.
In 2015, he contributed the song "Kyrie", a duet with Emmylou Harris, to the album Mercyland:
Then in 2016, White released a solo "Simple Song" for the album Southern Family by Dave Cobb.
His album Beulah was released on August 19, 2016.
In 2017, White guested on the song "It Ain't Over Yet" with Rodney Crowell and Rosanne Cash.
In 2018, White embarked on a little-publicized house concert tour to get feedback on new material.
His loyal fans obliged, and this culminated with the April 2019 release of his album The Hurting Kind.
White toured in 2019 with several Single Lock artists, including acclaimed newcomer Erin Rae.
